  "prompt": "What are the Yojana in Chhattisgarh?",
  "response": "Chhattisgarh, like other states in India, implements various **Yojanas (schemes)** aimed at the welfare and development of its citizens. These schemes cover sectors such as agriculture, education, health, women empowerment, social security, and infrastructure development. Below are some of the prominent Yojanas in Chhattisgarh:\n\n### **1. Agriculture and Farmer Welfare**\n- **Rajiv Gandhi Kisan Nyay Yojana:** Provides financial assistance to farmers for various crops, ensuring income support.\n- **Godhan Nyay Yojana:** Encourages cattle rearing and organic farming by purchasing cow dung from farmers and cattle owners.\n- **Mukhyamantri Khet Suraksha Yojana:** Focuses on the protection of agricultural land and crops from wild animals.\n\n### **2. Health and Nutrition**\n- **Mukhyamantri Haat Bazar Clinic Yojana:** Provides free health check-ups and treatment in rural weekly markets.\n- **Ayushman Bharat Yojana (National Health Protection Scheme):** Offers health insurance coverage to economically vulnerable families.\n- **Mukhyamantri Suposhan Abhiyan:** Aims to eradicate malnutrition in the state, especially among children and pregnant women.\n\n### **3. Education**\n- **Mukhyamantri Balak-Balika Cycle Yojana:** Distributes free bicycles to school-going children to encourage attendance.\n- **Mukhyamantri Medhavi Vidyarthi Yojana:** Provides financial assistance to meritorious students for higher education.\n- **Mukhyamantri Suposhan Sahyogi Yojana:** Supports nutritious meals for students in government schools.\n\n### **4. Women Empowerment**\n- **Mahtari Vandan Yojana:** A scheme to provide financial assistance to married women for their welfare.\n- **Kanyadan Yojana:** Offers financial assistance for the marriage of daughters from economically weaker families.\n- **Nari Shakti Yojana:** Focuses on the overall development and empowerment of women.\n\n### **5. Social Security**\n- **Mukhyamantri Pension Yojana:** Provides monthly pensions to senior citizens, widows, and disabled persons.\n- **Mukhyamantri Khadyanna Sahayta Yojana:** Offers subsidized food grains to economically weaker sections under the Public Distribution System (PDS).\n- **Mukhyamantri Samajik Suraksha Yojana:** Aims to provide financial security to unorganized sector workers.\n\n### **6. Infrastructure and Development**\n- **Mukhyamantri Gram Sadak Yojana:** Focuses on the construction and maintenance of rural roads.\n- **Mukhyamantri Shahri Awas Yojana:** Aims to provide affordable housing to urban poor.\n- **Swachh Bharat Mission (Chhattisgarh):** Promotes cleanliness and sanitation in rural and urban areas.\n\n### **7. Tribal Development**\n- **Mukhyamantri Vanbandhu Yojana:** Focuses on the welfare and development of tribal communities.\n- **Mukhyamantri Gramin Awas Yojana:** Provides housing facilities to rural families, especially tribals.\n\n### **8. Employment and Skill Development**\n- **Mukhyamantri Yuva Swabhiman Yojana:** Provides employment opportunities and skill development for unemployed youth.\n- **Mukhyamantri Shramik Card Yojana:** Offers benefits like insurance, pension, and financial assistance to laborers.\n\nThese schemes are regularly updated and new initiatives are introduced by the state government to address the specific needs of Chhattisgarh's population. For the latest information, you can visit the official website of the **Chhattisgarh Government** or contact relevant departments.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
